I have converted multiple screens in the application and structured them using reusable and responsive React Native components. First, I worked on the Home Screen, which acts as the main dashboard where users can see available cards and activated deals. From there, users can navigate to the Neighborhood Network screen, which includes the nearby offers feature and integrates Google Maps for location-based offers. I also implemented the Offers screen, where the offers are divided into In-Store and Online tabs, and added search functionality and skeleton loading for a better loading experience. When a user selects an offer, it navigates to the In-Store Details screen, where the user can view detailed information such as cashback, offer details, location with map view, and terms and conditions. Finally, I created the My Rewards screen, which displays the rewards earned by the user in a clean list layout with the merchant name, date, and reward amount. All screens were built using reusable components and responsive styling to ensure consistency and scalability across the app.